    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i see what u mean. but some people say the UN is basically just a tool for powerful countries to do whatever they want since the permanent members have all the veto power. do historians see those structural issues as a fatal flaw in the whole concept of international law, or is it just how global politics works?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
